100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 15, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing the ongoing tensions in Europe and efforts toward disarmament. In the United States, the controversy surrounding the Scopes Trial continued to reverberate, igniting debates over science and religion in schools. Meanwhile, in China, political instability deepened as warlord conflicts escalated, threatening the fragile unity of the nation.
